cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a deep learning method for left ventricle quantification from cardiac MR sequences using 3D spatio-temporal convolutions. This involves processing stacks of temporally adjacent slices using 3D convolutional kernels to incorporate the temporal dynamics of the heart. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it involves image analysis and processing. Additionally, the use of deep learning models suggests that it could also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The incorporation of temporal information through spatio-temporal convolutions could also suggest that it belongs to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the use of deep learning models for cardiac analysis could also suggest that it belongs to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
